review_blob: Simply incredible.  One of the best sours Ive ever had, and easily the best American sour.  Perfect balance of tartness and spice for a truly unique, refreshing drinking experience.
beer_name: Bruery Terreux Sour in the Rye

review_blob: Disappointing.  Doesnt quite commit to any style, stuck in purgatory.  Not flavorful enough.
Solid for the style. One of my go to sixpoint options, certainly one of their most popular offerings.  Nutty and malty.
Deep amber, with orange tint.  Smells of complex citrus profile, hops. Tastes like no other IPA -- rich and almost chocolatey.  Delicious, but a bit too sweet and heavy to drink easily.
beer_name: Laughing Dog Sneaky Pete Imperial IPA

review_blob: Deep, dark color.  Smells of bourbon barrels and burnt sugar.  Rich, delicious, like no other.
